trans:
2. any amounts due in respect of the Cooperation Agreement (there is no differentiation - any existing and future amounts due [redacted_name] against HDF in respect of the agreement) will be payable to the bank account indicated in the notice. This account belongs to [redacted_name]. [redacted_name] is authorized to make use of these funds unless [redacted_name] violates the terms of the Loan Agreement.
3. if [redacted_name] fails to pay their liabilities against the bank on time, the bank may satisfy themselves from the transferred claims. In this case, the Bank may turn to HDF to make payment to the bank account of PKO BP SA. This will be done upon delivering the notice on pursuance of secured claims (Schedule 3 to the Assignment Agreement).
4. if [redacted_name] violates the Loan Agreement in any other manner, the Bank may demand payment from HDF to PKO BP SA's account and hold the funds they received until the secured Bank's claims become payable.
5. PKO BP SA may satisfy themselves as follows by:
- issuing payment orders in favor of HDF;
- taking over the amounts paid by HDF;
- enforcing assigned claims;
- making further transfers, sales or any other disposal of the claims or raise their claims to the restructuring or bankruptcy proceedings;
6. [redacted_name] must advise the bank on any changes to the Cooperation Agreement.
(7) [redacted_name] has stated in the Assignment Agreement that HDF has no claims to be deducated against [redacted_name]
